'''''Star Wars Insider'' 79''' was the seventy-ninth issue released of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]''. It was released in [[January]] and [[February]] in [[2005]] under two separate covers.

It began shipping to subscribers on [[November 23]], and hit newsstands on [[December 7]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"Letter from the Editor"
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]"
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; [[The Cinema of George Lucas|One Picture at a Time]] {{C|by [[Jane Irene Kelly]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; Clone Wars Villains Face Their Fates: Days of Reckoning {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; Theed Royal Palace {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" &mdash; Six Degrees of Antilles, and You Must Unlearn What You Have Learned {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Would I Take a Trip On The Way-Back Machine? {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Anchorhead Arcade]]" ''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Jump to Lightspeed]]'' {{C|by [[Aki Sugawara]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; Episode III Toys: The Frenzy Is About To Begin {{C|by starwars.Hasbro.com}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; "Didn't We Just Leave This Party?" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 10
*"[[Laugh It Up, Fuzzball]]" {{C|by [[Randy Martinez]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>After a busy summer of filming, the postproduction crew at [[Industrial Light & Magic]] can officially begin to take care of business.</small>
*"[[The Wookiees Walk Amongst Us]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>Finally, five films and 27 years later, the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]] get their due on the big screen. ''Insider'' sits down with veteran ''Star Wars'' actor [[Peter Mayhew]] and newcomer [[Axel Dench]] to see what it takes to be a Wookiee.</small>
*"[[Kashyyyk Realized]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>Senior Concept Designer [[Ryan Church]] reveals how he and his team of exceptional artists are bringing the world of [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]] to life.</small>
*"[[A Visionary's Legacy: An Interview with Ralph McQuarrie]]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]]}}
*:<small>In the final installment of our three-part interview, [[Ralph McQuarrie]] talks about creating backdrops for the original trilogy as well as his contributions to the final film in the saga, [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']].</small>
*"[[Death in the Catacombs]]" {{C|by [[Mike W. Barr]]}}
*:<small>Unlikely allies&mdash;Jedi Knight [[Jyl Somtay]] and a smooth-talker smuggler [[Naj Pandoor]]&mdash;must venture into the dangerous caves of [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]] to capture a rogue scientist and recover a formidable [[Geonosian/Legends|Geonosian]] weapon.</small>

